==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|pleden}}, {{m|enm|plaiden}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|plaider||to plead, offer a plea}}, from {{m|fro|plait}}, from {{etyl|ML.|en}} {{m|la|placitum||a decree, sentence, suit, plea, etc.", in Classical {{etyl|la|en}}, "an opinion, determination, prescription, order; literally, that which is pleasing, pleasure}}, neuter of {{m|la|placitus}}, past participle of {{m|la|placere||to please}}.

