===Verb===
{{en-verb|pleads|pleading|pleaded|past_qual=North America, England|past2=pled|past2_qual=North America, Scotland|past3=plead|past3_qual=North America}}

# To present an argument, especially in a legal case.
#: {{ux|en|The defendant has decided to '''plead''' not guilty.}}
#* Bible, Job xvi. 21
#*: O that one might '''plead''' for a man with God, as a man pleadeth for his neighbour!
# To beg, beseech, or implore.
#: {{ux|en|He '''pleaded''' with me not to leave the house.}}

